subsection.def:
classification
                    (級別), in respect of a member, means the pay
                classification assigned to his rank by notice under section 5;

duty
                    (職責) includes active service, training and
                any voluntary duty;

member
                    (隊員) means any officer or member of the
                auxiliary forces;

rank
                    (職級) means any rank, grade, appointment or
                grouping of members;

subparagraph.content:
or any person authorized in writing by the Chief Executive, to
                        determine, in such circumstances as may be prescribed in the regulation, the
                        rate of pensions payable;

to appoint an actuary for the purpose of commuting a dependant pension
                        into a lump
                        sum;
